  <body>
    <h1>View Products</h1>
    <h2>Basic Path</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><p>The use case begins when the Inventory Manager selects "View Products".</p></li>
      <li><p>The software retrieves the last department looked at when he or she selected
	  "View Department." If there is no last department looked at the software uses
	  the department with the lowest department number.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software allows the Inventory Manager to change this department
	     in order to filter the different products.<p></li>
      <li><p>The software retrieves the products that have been selected.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software sorts the products by description.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software shows list of products to the Inventory Manager. The field's shown
	  are the product's SKU, description, UPC.</p></li>
      <li><p>The software allows the Inventory Manager to select one of the products, to
	     show more information about the product.</li>
      <li><p>The software also allows the Inventory Manager to filter the list based on description,
	     using regular expressions. </p></li>
    <h2>Alternate Paths</h2>
    <h3>DB Error</h3>
  </body>

